article.description: — Tristan Jarrett had 25 points as Jackson State beat Alabama State 60-44 on Monday night.
article.headline: Jarrett lifts Jackson St. past Alabama St. 60-44
article.linkText: Jarrett lifts Jackson St. past Alabama St. 60-44
article.story: MONTGOMERY, Ala. -- — Tristan Jarrett had 25 points as Jackson State beat Alabama State 60-44 on Monday night. Cainan McClelland had 14 points for Jackson State (1-5, 1-0 Southwestern Athletic Conference), which snapped its season-opening five-game losing streak. Jayveous McKinnis added 13 rebounds and three blocks. Kenny Strawbridge had 11 points and nine rebounds for the Hornets (0-2, 0-2). Jordan O’Neal added three blocks. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
